Epic Aircraft is a general aviation aircraft manufacturer headquartered in Bend, Oregon. The company produces the Epic E1000 single engine turboprop design.
Founded in 2004, the company initially manufactured and sold kits for the Epic LT. 
Epic went through bankruptcy in 2009, before being purchased by Russian businessman Vladislav Filev of S7 Airlines in 2012, and is now owned by Filev and his family through Cyprus-based MVF Key Investments Ltd.In 2013 the company discontinued taking orders for LT kits, to concentrate on certification of the E1000, which is based upon the LT. The E1000's certification from the FAA was completed in November 2019.

